messages.messageBody:
***OH A BIG LANGUAGE TOY!!! BIG ONE!!!!!!***

We've been Tranzalatin' text with the Textilizer. We've translated some
Shakespeare, Homer (Simpson) Joyce (Fetteroll) <g> Gansta Joyce, who'd
have thought?

We translated Farid ud-Din Attar's "Invocation" from "The Conference of
the Birds"

Invocation
we is busy wit tha luxury of th'n.
their gangsta n multiple faces bring
to us confusion we call knowledge. say:
god created tha world, pinned night ta day,
made mountains ta weigh it down, seas
to wash its face, mackin' creatures wit pleas
(the ancestors of praya) seek'n a place
in this mystery tizzle floats in endless space.
god set tha earth on tha bizzy of a bull,
the bull on a fizzle bustin' on a spool
of silva light so fine it is all like air;
that in turn rests on nuttin' there
but nuttin' thiznat nuttin' can share.
all th'n is but masks at gods B-to-tha-izzeck n call,
they is symbols thiznat instruct us tizzy god is all upside yo head.

--
And every time you hit "Translate" you get a slightly different version.

We've been translating Presidential speeches yo. Dylan has printed a few
out to save. Lot's of fun.

Deb L
